'''''Mygeeto Burns''''' was a [[Painting/Legends|painting]]<ref name="Celestia Galactica Photografica" /> created after [[104 ABY]]<ref name="Date" /> that depicted the [[Battle of Mygeeto]] during the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]] between the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]] and the [[Confederacy of Independent Systems/Legends|Confederacy of Independent Systems]]. In the center of the painting, a [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] stood on a rock with their [[Color/Legends|blue]] [[Lightsaber/Legends|lightsaber]] ignited, facing a Separatist [[LM-432 crab droid/Legends|LM-432 crab droid]]. Another figure knelt behind the Jedi. The background of the painting featured a [[Fire/Legends|burning]] [[Mygeeto/Legends|Mygeetan]] [[City/Legends|city]], and throughout it numerous Jedi were engaged in [[Ground warfare/Legends|combat]] with other crab droids.<ref name="Celestia Galactica Photografica" />

==Behind the scenes==
{{Quote|A series of full page paintings capture the amazing vistas around the galaxy, including a battle on Mygeeto, refugees on Alderaan, an immense Jedi museum and much more.|A preview description of "Celestia Galactica Photografica"|<ref name="Preview">{{SWArchive|url=eu/lit/comics/news20050315.html|text=Inside ''Star Wars: Visionaries''}}</ref>}}
''Mygeeto Burns'' was created for "[[Celestia Galactica Photografica]]," a collection of [[in-universe]] illustrations by [[Ryan Church]] included in the graphic novel anthology ''[[Star Wars: Visionaries]]''.<ref name="Celestia Galactica Photografica" /> The painting was first mentioned in a preview for ''Visionaries'' published on [[StarWars.com]] on [[March 15]], [[2005]]. The graphic novel was released on [[April 2]], 2005,<ref name="Preview" /> with ''Mygeeto Burns'' used as its cover illustration.<ref name="Celestia Galactica Photografica" /> The painting was also used as interior cover art in issues of the [[Star Wars Legends|''Star Wars'' Legends]] [[Epic Collection]] published by [[Marvel Comics]] that included other stories from ''Visionaries''. The first comic to do this was ''[[Star Wars Legends Epic Collection: The Clone Wars Vol. 1]]'',<ref name="Epic Collection">''[[Star Wars Legends Epic Collection: The Clone Wars Vol. 1]]''</ref> published on [[December 28]], [[2016]].<ref name="Marvel">{{Marvel|url=comics/collection/59777/star_wars_legends_epic_collection_the_clone_wars_vol_1_trade_paperback|text=Star Wars Legends Epic Collection: The Clone Wars Vol. 1 (Trade Paperback)}}</ref>

